</li><li class="postbit blockbody" id="post_6">
	<div class="header">
		<div class="datetime">September 19th, 2012, 02:06 PM</div>
		<span class="username">Eniarch</span>
	</div>
	
	
		<div class="title">Re: Dwarf Fortress: A Newbie Stream</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">1. Access/vision control.<br />
<br />
You don't want to give invaders the option to spread out, but they must have a path-able route to the fortress, or they stall. Simultaneously, you don't want them to have good sight-lines into the fortress, or they'll fire arrows into it from well-away from the doors.<br />
<br />
2. Doors are 1x1.<br />
<br />
You can do a two-door entryway, but the dwarves will pathfind to the closest route, so since my DEpot doesn't straddle the hallway, the dwarves would favor the southern door. I do intend to get a door up, but this episode (or possibly the next) will be somewhat controversial among the diehards, because I advocate for the &quot;seal the fortress when entry not in use&quot; method of play.<br />
<br />
I'm going to be handing out a large number of wooden training axes and engaging in mass deforestation in the next few episodes, because getting supplies of wood downstairs is a RIGHT F'in NAO level priority at this point. Our large trading session will attract massive migrant influx, and likely get us attacked in Spring of the new year, so it's &quot;fell the trees and get them into the stocks&quot; time.<br />
<br />
We'll also link up the floodgates and start up our well, and lay down some cage traps to deal with a possible early ambush, before starting on a metal/glass industry, a 1x1 walkway/pit combination, a drowning trap (if possible), and more. I've let the game go off pause with idle dwarves a few times when talking, and usually I wouldn't trade nearly as many goods as I did this time, so I'm expecting early Fun and a massive migrant wave shortly.<br />
<br />
Keep in mind, we'll be excavating a different route for later wagons, but early on, I need a wagon route, which is why the current entry hall is 3xN and not 1xN. 1xN is much safer, generally.<br />
<br />
@7pm local: <br />
<br />
I'll be firing the broadcast up in about an hour, if you folks are interested in watching.</blockquote>
	</div>
